\title{oncoscopR: Audit and Analysis Dashboard for Haematological Oncology Cohorts}
\description{
Reads tumour-documentation spreadsheets from haematological tumour centres
and computes quality and coverage indicators, OPS-8-544 complex chemotherapy
block counts, OPS-1-941 complex diagnostics counts, Kaplan-Meier analyses,
oncoprint and cytogenetics summaries, plus an interactive Shiny dashboard
for auditor live evaluation.
}
\details{
The entry point for interactive use is \code{\link[=onc_run_app]{onc_run_app()}}. Programmatic users
will mostly call the readers (\code{\link[=onc_read_cohort]{onc_read_cohort()}}, \code{\link[=onc_read_therapy]{onc_read_therapy()}},
\code{\link[=onc_read_diagnostics]{onc_read_diagnostics()}}) followed by the parsers
(\code{\link[=onc_prepare_therapy_blocks]{onc_prepare_therapy_blocks()}}, \code{\link[=onc_prepare_diagnostic_blocks]{onc_prepare_diagnostic_blocks()}},
\code{\link[=onc_parse_oncoprint]{onc_parse_oncoprint()}}, \code{\link[=onc_parse_cytogenetics]{onc_parse_cytogenetics()}}).

A fully synthetic example cohort is bundled and accessible via
\code{\link[=onc_example_path]{onc_example_path()}}.
